Former Texas Senator John Tower was killed in the crash of a commuter plane off the coast of 
Georgia. Senator Tower had been President Bush's nominee for Secretary of Defense. The Senate 
rejected the nomination following allegations of problems with alcohol and inappropriate 
dealings with defense contractors.</SUM>
